# Blurbs

## Using `B>` Syntax

B> This is a short blurb, only one line.

B> # A Longer Blurb
B>
B> This is a longer blurb.
B>
B> It can have multiple paragraphs.

## Using `{blurb}` Syntax

{blurb}
# A Longer Blurb

This is a longer blurb.

It can have multiple paragraphs.
{/blurb}

## Blurbs Containing Lists

{blurb}
This blurb includes a paragraph and an ordered list
1. This is the first item of the list
2. This is the second
3. And this is the third
{/blurb}

Below is just a blurb with an ordered list

{blurb}
1. This is the first item of the list
2. This is the second
3. And this is the third
{/blurb}

{blurb}
This blurb includes a paragraph and an unordered list
* This is the first item of the list
* This is the second
* And this is the third
{/blurb}

Below is just a blurb with an unordered list

{blurb}
* This is the first item of the list
* This is the second
* And this is the third
{/blurb}

## Other Blurb Classes

### Warning

{blurb, class: warning}
This is a warning!
{/blurb}

{class: warning}
B> This is a warning!

W> This is a warning!

### Discussion

{blurb, class: discussion}
This is a discussion!
{/blurb}

{class: discussion}
B> This is a discussion!

D> This is a discussion!

### Error

{blurb, class: error}
This is an error!
{/blurb}

{class: error}
B> This is an error!

E> This is an error!

### Information

{blurb, class: information}
This is an information!
{/blurb}

{class: information}
B> This is an information!

I> This is an information!

### Question

{blurb, class: question}
This is a question!
{/blurb}

{class: question}
B> This is a question!

Q> This is a question!

### Tip

{blurb, class: tip}
This is a tip!
{/blurb}

{class: tip}
B> This is a tip!

T> This is a tip!

### Exercise

{blurb, class: exercise}
This is a exercise!
{/blurb}

{class: exercise}
B> This is a exercise!

X> This is a exercise!

### Centered

{blurb, class: center}
This is a centered blurb
{/blurb}

{class: center}
B> This is a centered blurb.

C> This is a centered blurb.

### Icons for Blurbs

#### Car

{icon: car}
B> You can't spell carbon without it!

{blurb, class: tip, icon: car}
This is a tip with a car icon.
{/blurb}

{class: tip, icon: car}
B> This is a tip with a car icon.

{icon: car}
T> This is a tip with a car icon.

#### Leanpub Logo

{icon: leanpub}
B> Yes, we're in Font Awesome!

{blurb, class: center, icon: leanpub}
This is a centered blurb specified to have a leanpub icon, but centered overwrides it.
{/blurb}

{class: center, icon: leanpub}
B> This is a centered blurb specified to have a leanpub icon, but centered overwrides it.

{icon: leanpub}
C> This is a centered blurb specified to have a leanpub icon, but centered overwrides it.

#### GitHub Logo

{icon: github}
B> So is GitHub, of course. Unicorns.

{blurb, class: warning, icon: github}
This is a warning blurb with either a warning icon or a github icon (not sure which is more proper).
{/blurb}

{class: warning, icon: github}
B> This is a warning blurb with either a warning icon or a github icon (not sure which is more proper).

{icon: github}
W> This is a warning blurb with either a warning icon or a github icon (not sure which is more proper).

### Nonexistent Classes/Logos

{icon: iconthatdoesnotexistatall}
B> My icon is not here so should fall back to the warning

{class: classthatdoesnotexistatall}
B> my class does not exist so should fall back to the warning


